  "commentary": "With SPX at 6595.23 sitting right between the max negative gamma at 6590 (-25.6B) and max positive gamma at 6605 (+24.6B), dealers are currently buying the dip as spot hovers near the amplifying level, creating mechanical support. The breakout regime with -40B total GEX means any sustained move above 6605 will trigger dealer selling that accelerates upside momentum, while a break below the 6590 floor removes dealer buying support and opens downside to the next amplifying wall at 6580. Watch the 6590-6605 range closely—it's a 15-point battleground where dealer flow flips from buying to selling.\n\nBottom line: expect explosive moves once we break out of the tight 6590-6605 range in either direction.",
